%%{ init: { 'theme': 'base', 'sequence': { 'mirrorActors': false } } }%%

sequenceDiagram
    participant C as Client
    participant O as mini-oidc<br/>(OIDC Provider)
    participant E as Envoy Proxy<br/>(gateway-system)
    participant R as Router<br/>(mcp-system)
    participant B as Broker<br/>(mcp-system)
    participant S as MCP Server<br/>(mcp-test)

    Note over C,S: 1. Token Acquisition
    C->>O: GET /token
    O-->>C: {"access_token": "eyJ..."}

    Note over C,S: 2. Authentication (common to all requests)
    C->>E: POST /mcp<br/>Authorization: Bearer eyJ...

    Note over E: Istio RequestAuthentication<br/>validates JWT signature + issuer

    alt Invalid/missing token
        E-->>C: 401 Unauthorized<br/>WWW-Authenticate: Bearer<br/>(via Lua EnvoyFilter)
    end

    Note over E: ext_proc filter invoked

    E->>R: gRPC ext_proc request<br/>(headers + body)

    alt initialize / tools/list (aggregation path)
        Note over C,S: 3a. Initialize or tools/list → Broker aggregates

        Note over R: 1. Parse JSON-RPC body<br/>2. Method is "initialize" or "tools/list"<br/>3. Leave :authority unchanged<br/>(mcp.127-0-0-1.sslip.io)

        R-->>E: Headers unchanged<br/>:authority = mcp.127-0-0-1.sslip.io

        Note over E: Route matches default<br/>HTTPRoute → mcp-gateway-route

        E->>B: POST /mcp<br/>{"jsonrpc":"2.0","method":"tools/list"}

        Note over B: 1. Fan out to all registered<br/>upstream MCP servers<br/>2. Prefix each tool with server name<br/>(e.g. "greet" → "op_greet")<br/>3. Aggregate responses

        B->>S: POST /mcp<br/>{"jsonrpc":"2.0","method":"tools/list"}
        S-->>B: {"tools": [{"name":"greet"}, ...]}

        B-->>E: {"tools": [{"name":"op_greet"}, ...]}
        E-->>C: Aggregated tools/list response<br/>(all servers, prefixed tool names)

    else tools/call (direct routing path)
        Note over C,S: 3b. tools/call → Router sends direct to server

        Note over R: 1. Parse JSON-RPC body<br/>2. Extract tool name "op_greet"<br/>3. Strip prefix → "greet"<br/>4. Look up MCPServerRegistration<br/>5. Set :authority = test-server1.mcp.local

        R-->>E: Modified headers<br/>:authority = test-server1.mcp.local<br/>tool = "greet" (prefix stripped)

        Note over E: Route matches on :authority<br/>via HTTPRoute → test-server1 Service

        E->>S: POST /mcp<br/>{"jsonrpc":"2.0","method":"tools/call",<br/>"params":{"name":"greet"}}
        S-->>E: {"jsonrpc":"2.0","result":{...}}
        E-->>C: {"jsonrpc":"2.0","result":{...}}
    end
